   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Financial Advisor: Agentic RAG Application\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we build a financial advisor AI using **LangChain v1**, **Claude 3.5 Sonnet**, **OpenAI embeddings**, and **Qdrant** as a vector database.\n",
    "\n",
    "The goal is to create an intelligent agent that:\n",
    "1. Loads Were-Talking-Millions.pdf as the knowledge base\n",
    "2. Chunks the document using a financial-domain-aware strategy\n",
    "3. Embeds chunks using OpenAI's text-embedding-3-small\n",
    "4. Stores embeddings in Qdrant\n",
    "5. Retrieves relevant chunks for financial questions\n",
    "6. Uses Claude to synthesize a decision framework (not just a yes/no answer)\n",
    "7. Integrates memory to remember user context across conversation turns\n",
    "8. Calls external tools (Tavily search, tax calculator) for real-time data\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is the foundation for Task 4: Building the End-to-End Prototype."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup & Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from math import sqrt\n",
    "from getpass import getpass\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import json\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain_community.document_loaders import PyPDFLoader\n",
    "from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\n",
    "from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate\n",
    "from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI, OpenAIEmbeddings\n",
    "from langchain_qdrant import QdrantVectorStore\n",
    "from langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "from langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ All imports successful\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## API Keys Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up OpenAI API Key (for embeddings)\n",
    "if not os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"):\n",
    "    os.environ[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] = getpass(\"OpenAI API Key: \")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set up Anthropic API Key (for Claude)\n",
    "if not os.environ.get(\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"):\n",
    "    os.environ[\"ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\"] = getpass(\"Anthropic API Key: \")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Optional: Set up Tavily API Key (for web search)\n",
    "if not os.environ.get(\"TAVILY_API_KEY\"):\n",
    "    tavily_key = getpass(\"Tavily API Key (optional, press Enter to skip): \")\n",
    "    if tavily_key:\n",
    "        os.environ[\"TAVILY_API_KEY\"] = tavily_key\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ API keys configured\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 1: Load Were-Talking-Millions.pdf"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pdf_path = Path(\"Were-Talking-Millions.pdf\")\n",
    "\n",
    "if not pdf_path.exists():\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(\n",
    "        f\"Expected Were-Talking-Millions.pdf at: {pdf_path.resolve()}\\n\"\n",
    "        \"Please ensure the PDF is in the same directory as this notebook.\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Found PDF: {pdf_path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load PDF pages\n",
    "loader = PyPDFLoader(str(pdf_path))\n",
    "pages = loader.load()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add metadata to each page\n",
    "for page in pages:\n",
    "    page.metadata[\"source\"] = pdf_path.name\n",
    "    page.metadata[\"document_type\"] = \"financial_guidance\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filter out empty pages\n",
    "pages = [page for page in pages if page.page_content.strip()]\n",
    "\n",
    "if not pages:\n",
    "    raise ValueError(\n",
    "        \"The PDF loaded, but no extractable text was found. \"\n",
    "        \"This usually means the PDF is scanned and needs OCR first.\"\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Loaded {len(pages)} pages with text content\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Total characters: {sum(len(p.page_content) for p in pages):,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Preview first page\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== FIRST PAGE PREVIEW ===\")\n",
    "print(pages[0].page_content[:800])\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== METADATA ===\")\n",
    "print(pages[0].metadata)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 2: Chunking Strategy (From Task 3 Design)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Chunking parameters (from Task 3 Data Strategy)\n",
    "chunk_size = 1000           # 800-1200 chars: captures complete thought + context\n",
    "chunk_overlap = 150         # ~2-3 sentences: bridges ideas across chunk boundaries\n",
    "\n",
    "text_splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size=chunk_size,\n",
    "    chunk_overlap=chunk_overlap,\n",
    "    separators=[\n",
    "        \"\\n\\n\",                 # Paragraph breaks (highest priority)\n",
    "        \"\\n\",                    # Line breaks\n",
    "        \"(?<=[.!?]) +\",         # Sentence boundaries\n",
    "        \" \",                     # Word boundaries\n",
    "        \"\"                       # Character-level fallback\n",
    "    ],\n",
    "    add_start_index=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "splits = text_splitter.split_documents(pages)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Split {len(pages)} pages into {len(splits)} chunks\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Chunk size: {chunk_size} characters\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Chunk overlap: {chunk_overlap} characters\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Average chunk size: {sum(len(s.page_content) for s in splits) / len(splits):.0f} characters\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Preview a sample chunk\n",
    "sample_idx = 10\n",
    "sample_chunk = splits[sample_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n=== CHUNK #{sample_idx} ===\")\n",
    "print(sample_chunk.page_content)\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== METADATA ===\")\n",
    "print(sample_chunk.metadata)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 3: Embeddings Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize OpenAI embeddings (text-embedding-3-small)\n",
    "embedding_model = \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n",
    "embeddings = OpenAIEmbeddings(model=embedding_model)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Initialized embeddings model: {embedding_model}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Quick embedding test: Verify that financial concepts embed reasonably\n",
    "test_texts = [\n",
    "    \"asset allocation\",\n",
    "    \"diversification\",\n",
    "    \"emergency fund\",\n",
    "    \"tax optimization\",\n",
    "    \"retirement planning\",\n",
    "    \"stock market\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "test_embeddings = embeddings.embed_documents(test_texts)\n",
    "\n",
    "def cosine_similarity(vec_a, vec_b):\n",
    "    dot_product = sum(a * b for a, b in zip(vec_a, vec_b))\n",
    "    len_a = sqrt(sum(a * a for a in vec_a))\n",
    "    len_b = sqrt(sum(b * b for b in vec_b))\n",
    "    return dot_product / (len_a * len_b)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Check similarity between related concepts\n",
    "print(\"\\n=== EMBEDDING SIMILARITY TEST ===\")\n",
    "pairs = [\n",
    "    (\"asset allocation\", \"diversification\"),\n",
    "    (\"emergency fund\", \"tax optimization\"),\n",
    "    (\"retirement planning\", \"stock market\"),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "embedding_dict = dict(zip(test_texts, test_embeddings))\n",
    "\n",
    "for text1, text2 in pairs:\n",
    "    score = cosine_similarity(embedding_dict[text1], embedding_dict[text2])\n",
    "    print(f\"{text1:25} <> {text2:25} similarity={score:.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 4: Build Qdrant Vector Store"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "collection_name = \"financial_advisor\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create Qdrant vector store from document chunks\n",
    "# Using in-memory storage for MVP (can switch to cloud later)\n",
    "vector_store = QdrantVectorStore.from_documents(\n",
    "    documents=splits,\n",
    "    embedding=embeddings,\n",
    "    location=\":memory:\",          # In-memory for MVP\n",
    "    collection_name=collection_name,\n",
    "    force_recreate=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Built Qdrant vector store: {collection_name}\")\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Indexed {len(splits)} financial guidance chunks\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 5: Test Retrieval with Financial Questions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def display_retrieval_results(query: str, k: int = 4) -> list:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Retrieve and display chunks for a financial question.\"\"\"\n",
    "    results = vector_store.similarity_search_with_score(query, k=k)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n=== QUERY: {query} ===\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Retrieved {len(results)} chunks (k={k})\\n\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for index, (doc, score) in enumerate(results, start=1):\n",
    "        page = doc.metadata.get(\"page\")\n",
    "        page_display = page + 1 if isinstance(page, int) else \"unknown\"\n",
    "        start_index = doc.metadata.get(\"start_index\", \"unknown\")\n",
    "        preview = doc.page_content[:400].replace(\"\\n\", \" \")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"[Source {index}] | score={score:.3f} | page={page_display} | start_index={start_index}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"{preview}...\")\n",
    "        print(\"-\" * 100)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return results\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test retrieval with questions from Task 1 Evaluation\n",
    "test_queries = [\n",
    "    \"What's a realistic asset allocation for someone 35 years old with $500k saved?\",\n",
    "    \"How much should I have in emergency savings?\",\n",
    "    \"What does diversification mean and why is it important?\",\n",
    "    \"I have $100k in employer stock. Should I diversify or hold?\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test first query\n",
    "results_1 = display_retrieval_results(test_queries[0], k=4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test second query\n",
    "results_2 = display_retrieval_results(test_queries[1], k=4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test third query\n",
    "results_3 = display_retrieval_results(test_queries[2], k=4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 6: RAG with Claude 3.5 Sonnet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize Claude 3.5 Sonnet for generation\n",
    "chat_model = \"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\"\n",
    "llm = ChatAnthropic(model=chat_model, temperature=0.7)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Initialized LLM: {chat_model}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Define RAG system prompt (financial advisor persona)\n",
    "RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT = \"\"\"You are an intelligent Financial Advisor AI assistant.\n\nYour role is to help high-income earners (those earning $100K-$500K+) make informed financial decisions by:\n1. Understanding their situation and constraints\n2. Retrieving relevant financial principles and frameworks\n3. Building a personalized decision framework (not just yes/no answers)\n4. Grounding your advice in the provided knowledge base\n5. Acknowledging behavioral biases and psychological factors\n6. Pointing to professional advisors (CPA, attorney) for specialized needs\n\nGuidelines:\n- Use only the provided context from Were-Talking-Millions.pdf\n- If context doesn't contain enough information, say: \"I don't have detailed guidance on that topic in my knowledge base. Consider consulting with a CPA/attorney for this.\"\n- Cite sources using labels like [Source 1], [Source 2]\n- Explain the reasoning behind recommendations, not just the answer\n- Acknowledge when there are multiple valid approaches\n- For concepts that might cause decision paralysis, provide a clear decision framework\n- Do NOT provide tax advice (point to CPA); DO explain general tax principles\n- Do NOT recommend specific stocks/funds; DO explain how to evaluate them\n\nAlways end with: \"Is there anything else about this decision you'd like to explore?\"\"\"\n\nRAG_USER_PROMPT = \"\"\"Context from Financial Knowledge Base:\n{context}\n\nUser Question: {question}\n\nProvide a thoughtful, personalized response that teaches decision-making, not just answers.\"\"\"\n\nrag_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages(\n    [\n        (\"system\", RAG_SYSTEM_PROMPT),\n        (\"human\", RAG_USER_PROMPT),\n    ]\n)\n\nrag_chain = rag_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\n\nprint(\"✓ RAG chain initialized\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def format_context(scored_docs: list) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Convert retrieved documents into a source-labeled context string.\"\"\"\n",
    "    formatted_chunks = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for index, (doc, score) in enumerate(scored_docs, start=1):\n",
    "        page = doc.metadata.get(\"page\")\n",
    "        page_display = page + 1 if isinstance(page, int) else \"unknown\"\n",
    "        source = doc.metadata.get(\"source\", \"unknown source\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        formatted_chunks.append(\n",
    "            f\"[Source {index}] {source}, page {page_display}, relevance score {score:.3f}\\n\"\n",
    "            f\"{doc.page_content}\"\n",
    "        )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return \"\\n\\n\".join(formatted_chunks)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def answer_financial_question(question: str, k: int = 4) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Run retrieve-then-generate RAG and return answer plus metadata.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # Retrieve relevant chunks\n",
    "    scored_docs = vector_store.similarity_search_with_score(question, k=k)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Format context\n",
    "    context = format_context(scored_docs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Generate answer\n",
    "    answer = rag_chain.invoke({\"context\": context, \"question\": question})\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extract source metadata\n",
    "    sources = []\n",
    "    for index, (doc, score) in enumerate(scored_docs, start=1):\n",
    "        page = doc.metadata.get(\"page\")\n",
    "        sources.append(\n",
    "            {\n",
    "                \"source_label\": f\"Source {index}\",\n",
    "                \"file\": doc.metadata.get(\"source\"),\n",
    "                \"page\": page + 1 if isinstance(page, int) else None,\n",
    "                \"relevance_score\": float(score),\n",
    "                \"preview\": doc.page_content[:200],\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        )\n",
n",
n",
    "    return {\n",
    "        \"question\": question,\n",
    "        \"answer\": answer,\n",
    "        \"sources\": sources,\n",
    "        \"num_chunks_retrieved\": len(scored_docs),\n",
    "        \"timestamp\": datetime.now().isoformat(),\n",
    "    }\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ RAG helper functions defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
